- id: scraped-q-279
  source: General Data Engineering
  category: Big Data
  niche: 
  difficulty: MEDIUM
  question: How does Pipeline work in Apache Spark?
  answer: A Pipeline is a sequence of stages. Each stage in Pipeline can be a Transformer or an Estimator. We run these stages in an order. Initially a DataFrame is passed as an input to Pipeline. This DataFrame keeps on transforming with each stage of Pipeline. Most of the time, Runtime checking is done on DataFrame passing through the Pipeline. We can also save a Pipeline to a disk. It can be re-read from disk a later point of time.
