  difficulty: MEDIUM
  question: What is an Accumulator in Apache Spark?
  answer: An Accumulator is a variable in Spark that can be added only through an associative and commutative operation. An Accumulator can be supported in parallel. It is generally used to implement a counter or cumulative sum. We can create numeric type Accumulators by default in Spark.An Accumulator variable can be named as well as unnamed.
- id: scraped-q-286
