  source: General Data Engineering
  category: Databases & SQL
  niche: 
  difficulty: MEDIUM
  question: What is the use of .hiverc file in Hive?
  answer: In Hive, .hiverc is the initialization file. This file is loaded when we start Command Line Interface for Hive. We can set the initial values of parameters in this file.
- id: scraped-q-531
  source: General Data Engineering
  category: Databases & SQL
  niche: 
  difficulty: MEDIUM
  question: How will you run Unix commands from Hive?
  answer: We can run Unix commands from Hive shell by using ! sign. We have to append ! sign before a unix command. E.g. For using date command we have to run it as !date in Hive shell.
- id: scraped-q-532
  source: General Data Engineering
  category: Databases & SQL
  niche: 
  difficulty: MEDIUM
  question: What is the purpose of USE command in Hive?
  answer: In Hive we have to call USE command before running and hive queries. USE command sets the current database on which query statements will be executed. We can call USE default to set the database to default database. Or we can call USE database_name to set the database on which we want to run the queries.
- id: scraped-q-533
  source: General Data Engineering
  category: Databases & SQL
  niche: 
  difficulty: MEDIUM
  question: What is the precedence order in Hive configuration?
  answer: |
    In Hive we can use following precedence order to set the configurable properties.
    Hive SET command has the highest priority
    -hiveconf option from Hive Command Line
    hive-site.xml file
    hive-default.xml file
    hadoop-site.xml file
    hadoop-default.xml file
