  question: Can Hadoop be compared to Nosql Database like Cassandra?
  answer: Though NOSQL is the closet technology that can be compared to Hadoop, it has its own pros and cons. There is no DFS in NOSQL. Hadoop is not a database. It’s a file system (HDFS) and distributed programming framework (MapReduce).
